item.title: Roseanne Barr 'Can't Bear' to Watch 'The Conners' After Exit
item.description: After The Conners killed off Roseanne Barr’s eponymous character in 2018, the comedian is not interested in watching the sitcom. “I just can’t bear it, so I don’t,” Barr, 70, told The Los Angeles Times in an interview published on Thursday, February 9. “When they killed my character off, that was a message to me, knowing that I’m mentally ill or have mental health issues, that they did want me to commit suicide.” She continued: “They killed my character … And all of that was to say thank you for bringing 28 million viewers, which they never had before and will never see again.

item.title: How Patrick Mahomes' Kneel-Downs Cost Super Bowl LIV Bettors
item.description: Kansas City Chiefs quarterback Patrick Mahomes shrugged off three sloppy quarters of football and did just enough to lead his team to their first Super Bowl championship in 50 years. item.description: Drake will add another bullet point to his historic resume when he performs at the legendary Apollo Theater in Harlem, N.Y for the first time on Nov. 11. item.title: Ellie Goulding's Fifty Shades Music Video Shows Sexy Movie Clips
item.description: Hurry up, already! With only weeks to go until the much anticipated movie Fifty Shades of Grey premieres in theaters on Valentine’s Day, Saturday, Feb. 14, fans have been given another tantalizing peek at the super-steamy scenes thanks to Ellie Goulding‘s new music video. Goulding’s new song, “Love Me Like You Do,” will appear on the soundtrack for the movie adaptation of E L James‘ best-selling book, and the music video to accompany the track reveals a host of never-before-seen clips of the movie, including quick flashes into Christian Grey’s BDSM Red Room of Pain.

item.title: Hailey Bieber's Skincare Products Are Leaving Fans Furious (And In Pain)
item.description: Prior to tying the knot with her husband, Justin Bieber in 2018, Hailey Bieber was best known for her modeling career. In October 2014, she made her first runway debut for Topshop and French fashion designer Sonia Rykiel. After making a breakthrough in her modeling career, Hailey went on to land appearances in several high-profile publications, including Vogue (2015) and Teen Vogue, as well as shooting for fashion brands such as Ralph Lauren, Tommy Hilfiger, Jimmy Choo, and Tiffany.

While Taylor openly discussed their relationship and had positive things to say about Joe, he tended to focus on his need for privacy and defended his decision to keep their relationship out of the public eye.

item.title: Michael Jackson's Mom Demands $560,000 From His Estate As She Fights Executors
item.description: Highlights Michael Jackson's family is still embroiled in a legal battle over his million-dollar estate, with his mother, Katherine, requesting half a million dollars to cover legal expenses wrongfully billed to her. Jackson's estate continues to generate significant revenue from various sources, contributing to its posthumous success and estimated worth of over $1 billion. Despite leaving his estate to his children, Jackson set up a separate trust to care for his mother, Katherine, but the executors of the estate are claiming to have made substantial profits for Jackson's legacy, leading to ongoing legal disputes.

item.title: Alan Jackson Plans for More Music to Come Amid Health Struggles
item.description: He’ll try! Alan Jackson revealed he has plans to release more music amid his ongoing battle with Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease.  “Yes. I would hope so. I mean, I may not have toured much, but, like I said, the creative part jumps out every now and then,” Jackson, 64, said on the Tuesday, February 21, episode of the “In Joy Life” podcast, which is hosted by daughter Mattie Jackson. “I’m always scribbling down ideas and thinking about melodies and I feel like there’ll be some more music to come, yes.

item.title: Alexa Bliss Believes Her Match With Ronda Rousey Can Headline SummerSlam
item.description: The WWE Raw Women’s Champion Alexa Bliss believes that her upcoming match with Ronda Rousey at WWE SummerSlam can headline the event. “You have the five-time WWE Champion going up against a UFC Hall of Famer. Why not let it be the main event?” she told Mirror Sport. “I do I believe that with the women’s evolution going the way it is, then why not? But if not, then it is still great that I get to have a match with Ronda, who is making her SummerSlam debut.

item.description: Almost a year to the day after playing host to Prince Harry and Meghan Markle‘s nuptials, St George’s Chapel in Windsor was the scene of yet another royal wedding on Saturday, May 18. Lady Gabriella Marina Alexandra Ophelia Windsor (“Ella” to those in the know) married financier Thomas Kingston in the company of Queen Elizabeth II, Prince Harry (sans the Duchess and baby Archie), Pippa Middleton and more, and now we have the scoop on her stunning bespoke wedding dress by Luisa Beccaria.

item.description: Bill Zanker Wiki Biography Bill Zanker is an American entrepreneur, best known for being the founder of the adult education company The Learning Annex. He is married to Deborah Zanker, and the two have three children, Ediva Zanker (born 1993), Dylan Zanker (born 1995) and Vera Zanker (born 1996). The family currently resides in Utah.Zanker grew up in Teaneck, New Jersey. He earned a bachelor of arts degree from the Hebrew University of Jerusalem and majored in film towards a master’s degree at The New School.

item.title: Toni Braxton Retires From Music: "My Heart Isn't in It Anymore"
item.description: Toni Braxton's twenty-year music career has come to an end. The "He Wasn't Man Enough" singer made the announcement during a Friday, Feb. 8, appearance on Good Morning America. "It's not affecting me, making me feel that thing I've always felt when I perform. It's leaving me," Braxton said. "I'm not sure what's going on in my life. Maybe a female mid-life crisis? My heart isn't in it anymore. I hate to say that.
